Memory Lane?

03:28.580 --> 03:29.620
No.

03:30.830 --> 03:33.120
You know what -- you go ahead
and throw him that party.

03:33.120 --> 03:34.750
I'm gonna have
nothing to do with it,

03:34.750 --> 03:37.750
because I learned --
dealing with Pops,

03:37.750 --> 03:39.580
you'll only
get burned.

03:39.580 --> 03:42.420
So keep my name
out of it.

03:42.420 --> 03:43.920
Uh, I will.

03:43.920 --> 03:45.750
Except we have
the same name,

03:45.750 --> 03:47.790
so you will see the words
"Andre Johnson"

03:47.790 --> 03:48.920
on the e-vite.

03:50.170 --> 03:53.000
Rainbow. I need to use
your computer.

03:53.000 --> 03:55.500
Taye Diggs started
following me online,

03:55.500 --> 03:58.960
and you know Taye Diggs
just doesn't follow anyone.

04:02.420 --> 04:04.880
Um, let me just finish,
and then it's all yours.

04:04.880 --> 04:06.880
Well, what are you watching?
Is it dumb?

04:06.880 --> 04:08.330
No, it's not dumb.

04:08.330 --> 04:10.170
It is an interview
with Shonda Rhimes

04:10.170 --> 04:12.420
about how she committed
to a year

04:12.420 --> 04:15.120
of saying "Yes" to her children
to get to know them better.

04:15.120 --> 04:16.790
So, yes, it's dumb.

04:16.790 --> 04:18.420
No. No, Ruby,
it's not.

04:18.420 --> 04:21.960
Listen, when I was working,
I created this habit

04:21.960 --> 04:25.670
of just reflexively saying "No"
to the children.

04:25.670 --> 04:28.000
Hey, Mom, do you want to play
"Operation" with us?

04:28.000 --> 04:30.000
No.
I just operated.

04:30.000 --> 04:32.540
And in my business, a red nose
is a symptom of sepsis.

04:32.540 --> 04:35.420
♪♪

04:35.420 --> 04:37.290
And then I watched
this video,

04:37.290 --> 04:39.460
and I realized
I'm not working anymore,

04:39.460 --> 04:40.920
and I'm still
saying "No"!

04:40.920 --> 04:42.170
Hey, Mom.
Yeah?

04:42.170 --> 04:43.670
Do you want to play
"Settlers of Catan" with us?

04:44.620 --> 04:45.710
Yes.

04:46.880 --> 04:48.880
Yes, I do!

04:48.880 --> 04:50.420
-All right. Great.
-Okay.

04:50.420 --> 04:51.290
See?

04:51.290 --> 04:54.170
My year
of saying "Yes"...

04:54.170 --> 04:55.580
has begun.

04:55.580 --> 04:57.330
♪♪

04:57.330 --> 04:59.880
Okay, where are we
on the Atlantis account?

05:01.580 --> 05:04.000
It's pronounced
"Atlan-ta."

05:04.000 --> 05:06.500
No, it's Atlantis --

05:06.500 --> 05:07.880
a beautiful resort
in the Bahamas.

05:07.880 --> 05:09.880
Now, what have you got?

05:09.880 --> 05:12.170
Well, it depends.

05:12.170 --> 05:14.880
Is there a "Magic City"
strip club in the Bahamas?

05:14.880 --> 05:16.170
There is not.

05:16.170 --> 05:18.210
Then I may need
more time.

05:18.210 --> 05:20.040
Look, I told you,
I'm not interested.

05:20.040 --> 05:21.880
Please stop calling me!

05:21.880 --> 05:23.080
Telemarketer, huh?

05:23.080 --> 05:25.290
No -- my son.

05:25.290 --> 05:27.080
He wants me to plan
this birthday party for Pops,

05:27.080 --> 05:28.620
who's turning 65.

05:28.620 --> 05:30.620
Your dad is turning 65?

05:30.620 --> 05:32.750
My God, he must be
the oldest living black person.

05:32.750 --> 05:34.960
Why don't you want to throw
a party for your dad?

05:34.960 --> 05:37.710
Because my Pops doesn't deserve
to be celebrated.

05:37.710 --> 05:39.290
Lot of anger
packed there.

05:39.290 --> 05:41.750
It's gonna push into your
prostate and turn into cancer.

05:41.750 --> 05:44.040
I just don't believe in giving
participation trophies,

05:44.040 --> 05:46.290
especially to a man
who barely participated.

05:46.290 --> 05:48.210
I thought you were cool
with your father.

05:48.210 --> 05:51.080
I mean, we cool now,
but, you know...

05:51.080 --> 05:53.120
growing up, we wasn't.

05:53.120 --> 05:56.330
He -- He stole,
he cheated, he gambled.

05:56.330 --> 05:58.620
So what? My father stole,
cheated, and gambled,

05:58.620 --> 06:00.250
but it was an honor
to throw him a party.

06:00.250 --> 06:01.710
Oh, that's right.

06:01.710 --> 06:05.830
A weekend of transactional sex
at the Belushi suite.

06:05.830 --> 06:08.290
The second-best
50th birthday party I ever had.

06:08.290 --> 06:10.170
Why are you being
such a baby, Dre?

06:10.170 --> 06:12.040
Just grow up
and help your father.

06:12.040 --> 06:15.420
Look, it's a son's duty
to honor thy father.

06:15.420 --> 06:16.620
It says so right there
in the Bible.

06:16.620 --> 06:17.960
It's true.

06:17.960 --> 06:20.250
Right there with
not eating shellfish

06:20.250 --> 06:22.670
and not sitting next to
a menstruating woman.

06:22.670 --> 06:25.330
It sounds like I'm making
this stuff up, but...

06:25.330 --> 06:27.540
the Bible's weird.

06:27.540 --> 06:30.000
I had to admit,
the guys at work were right.

06:30.000 --> 06:31.790
I needed to help Junior out.

06:31.790 --> 06:33.710
Dre: Put it away!
I'm coming in!

06:35.960 --> 06:37.290
All right.

06:37.290 --> 06:39.040
Let's plan Pops' party.

06:39.040 --> 06:40.290
Together?

06:40.290 --> 06:42.040
That sounds amazing!

06:42.040 --> 06:44.580
I have so many ideas
that I need to run by someone.

06:44.580 --> 06:46.040
Okay.

06:46.040 --> 06:48.580
Let's talk e-vites,
themes, centerpieces.

06:48.580 --> 06:50.420
This is not
a bar mitzvah, boy.

06:50.420 --> 06:53.080
And Pops' friends will not
respond to e-vites.

06:53.080 --> 06:56.120
Great.
So paperless posts, then.

06:57.250 --> 06:59.620
I can feel you giving me
prostate cancer.

07:04.620 --> 07:05.960
So, are we ready to plan
Pops' surprise party?

07:05.960 --> 07:08.080
Yeah, but, baby,
be quick about it.

07:08.080 --> 07:10.460
I got to meet
my part-time lover/

07:10.460 --> 07:13.250
full-time
financial advisor.

07:13.250 --> 07:14.830
Yeah, and I noticed
your neighbor

07:14.830 --> 07:16.290
had left their gate
unlocked.

07:16.290 --> 07:19.000
Ohh. I can't believe
I signed up for this.

07:19.000 --> 07:21.210
Uh, maybe we should
just get started.

07:21.210 --> 07:22.710
It's Tuesday,
which means

07:22.710 --> 07:24.670
Pops is either
at Commerce Casino

07:24.670 --> 07:26.710
or waiting on line
for "Ellen" tickets.

07:26.710 --> 07:28.460
So, what do you need
from us?

07:28.460 --> 07:31.580
I want to make this party
a tribute to Pops,

07:31.580 --> 07:34.290
but I'm having a hard time
getting his friends to come.

07:34.290 --> 07:36.120
So, do you think
you can make it?

07:36.120 --> 07:38.040
Man:
What, this Saturday, huh?
Mm-hmm.

07:38.040 --> 07:39.330
Hmm...

07:39.330 --> 07:41.080
It might be hard
for me to make that.

07:42.670 --> 07:44.420
You're having a hard time
getting his friends to come

07:44.420 --> 07:45.920
because they're all bums.

07:45.920 --> 07:47.290
Hey, whoa, whoa.
What?

07:47.290 --> 07:49.250
No, no. He's not
talking about you.

07:49.250 --> 07:51.540
Oh, I'm most definitely
talking about you.

07:51.540 --> 07:55.380
And Pookie and Ray Ray
and Cool Breeze.

07:55.380 --> 07:57.380
Pops has a friend
named "Cool Breeze"?

07:57.380 --> 08:01.080
Every black man has
a friend named "Cool Breeze."

08:01.080 --> 08:02.710
-I don't.
-Oh.

08:02.710 --> 08:05.420
Sounds like you just
got yourself a nickname --

08:05.420 --> 08:07.540
Cool Breeze.
-Ooh.

08:07.540 --> 08:09.210
Ohh. Wow.

08:10.380 --> 08:11.790
I remember that car.

08:11.790 --> 08:14.670
You must have plenty
of great memories, huh?

08:14.670 --> 08:16.210
Just you and Pops.

08:16.210 --> 08:18.790
One A&W Root Beer float,

08:18.790 --> 08:20.830
two straws.

08:20.830 --> 08:23.790
Just a boy and his dad
cruising up the coast,

08:23.790 --> 08:25.790
listening to
the Beach Boys.

08:25.790 --> 08:27.790
Okay, for the last time,
I told you --

08:27.790 --> 08:29.960
I am not doing that
with you.

08:29.960 --> 08:31.790
It's weird!

08:31.790 --> 08:33.420
And I could give a damn
about that car.

08:33.420 --> 08:36.620
He -- He loved that car
more than he loved me.

08:36.620 --> 08:40.080
It was always washed,
on new tires.

08:40.080 --> 08:43.420
