12:17.420 --> 12:19.790
go to the club, and double it.

12:19.790 --> 12:22.170
♪ But now I'm cool ♪

12:22.170 --> 12:24.250
♪ I didn't make it, sugar ♪

12:24.250 --> 12:27.830
Men hid their wallets
and guarded their honies,

12:27.830 --> 12:31.170
'cause Earl's taking wives
and everybody's money.

12:31.170 --> 12:34.040
♪ I come up hard,
but that's okay ♪

12:34.040 --> 12:38.250
-Ohh!
-Yes!

12:38.250 --> 12:40.580
His dice were hitting so hard,

12:40.580 --> 12:44.080
these heifers' heads
nearly exploded.

12:44.080 --> 12:46.670
But Earl was rolling 7s
all night

12:46.670 --> 12:48.330
Come on!
because his dice were loaded.

12:48.330 --> 12:49.750
Negro, let me see
them di--

12:49.750 --> 12:51.500
Uh-oh!

12:51.500 --> 12:52.880
Oh, hell no!

12:54.420 --> 12:55.710
Roundhouse!

12:55.710 --> 12:58.040
♪♪

12:58.040 --> 12:59.080
Suckah!

13:01.000 --> 13:04.620
Just when you thought he bit
off more than he could chew,

13:04.620 --> 13:09.420
he beat back those Negroes
with his ghetto kung fu.

13:09.420 --> 13:12.670
All their barks weren't
as bad as Earl's bite,

13:12.670 --> 13:15.710
'cause those fools brought
knives to a nunchuck fight!

13:18.420 --> 13:21.210
Earl beat everybody
but forgot about Crystal.

13:21.210 --> 13:23.120
Nice doing business
with ya.

13:23.120 --> 13:26.460
He knew kung fu,
but she knew kung pistol.

13:26.460 --> 13:28.790
Sorry, Daddy.
I need to take everything.

13:28.790 --> 13:33.880
♪♪

13:33.880 --> 13:35.750
Damn.

13:35.750 --> 13:38.670
I had no idea that's how
Pops made his side money.

13:38.670 --> 13:40.960
Hold on. So, that was
actually a true story?

13:40.960 --> 13:42.460
Oh, yeah.

13:42.460 --> 13:44.420
'Least, that's what
the police report said.

13:44.420 --> 13:46.580
I didn't realize
Pops was such a con man.

13:46.580 --> 13:47.670
Fake IDs --

13:47.670 --> 13:49.000
"Rocco Shabazz"?

13:49.000 --> 13:51.250
"Pinky Gonzales"?

13:51.250 --> 13:52.920
"Jesus Berkowitz"?

13:52.920 --> 13:54.500
I remember these.

13:54.500 --> 13:56.790
It took us forever
to get these just right.

13:56.790 --> 13:58.290
They still didn't work.

13:58.290 --> 14:00.710
He got arrested at the airport
immediately.

14:00.710 --> 14:01.540
Sure did.

14:01.540 --> 14:03.330
Arrested?

14:03.330 --> 14:05.080
I feel like I don't
even know this guy.

14:05.080 --> 14:07.670
He stole mattresses,
gambled,

14:07.670 --> 14:10.080
forged passports,
roundhoused.

14:10.080 --> 14:11.880
Is his name
even "Pops"?

14:11.880 --> 14:14.920
Hey. Settle down,
Cool Breeze.

14:14.920 --> 14:16.790
Yeah, I-I-I'm cool.
I'm --

14:16.790 --> 14:18.330
I'm just out.

14:18.330 --> 14:19.380
I'm not celebrating
this guy.

14:19.380 --> 14:21.750
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey.
Hold on, man.

14:21.750 --> 14:23.710
So, you're saying
you're not on Pops?

14:23.710 --> 14:27.290
Are you not hearing the same
stories that I'm hearing?

14:27.290 --> 14:29.580
Put yourself
in his shoes.

14:29.580 --> 14:31.080
Think about it.

14:31.080 --> 14:34.620
Pops tried to escape
the racism of the Deep South

14:34.620 --> 14:37.790
and fell into the racism
of Deep South Central.

14:37.790 --> 14:40.670
Sam Yorty was mayor,
Ronald Reagan was governor,

14:40.670 --> 14:42.380
and they ain't never seen
a black man

14:42.380 --> 14:44.790
they didn't want
to break in half.

14:44.790 --> 14:49.120
Pops' generation was
the last hired and first fired.

14:49.120 --> 14:52.330
And remember, he didn't
make a lot of money,

14:52.330 --> 14:56.290
so he had to stretch it as far
as he could for his family --

14:56.290 --> 14:58.620
especially around the holidays.

14:58.620 --> 15:00.790
That's why he had
his side hustles --

15:00.790 --> 15:03.290
to turn 1 dollar into 2.

15:03.290 --> 15:07.290
Look, Pops wasn't perfect,
but he was more than most.

15:07.290 --> 15:09.330
I remember once,
I had a friend over,

15:09.330 --> 15:12.080
and he asked who that man
in the hallway was.

15:12.080 --> 15:14.250
I said, "That's my dad."

15:14.250 --> 15:17.170
He had never seen a dad before.

15:17.170 --> 15:19.120
I was one
of only a couple of friends

15:19.120 --> 15:22.000
who even knew their dad.

15:22.000 --> 15:24.000
Yeah, it's easy
to judge Pops now

15:24.000 --> 15:27.460
because he survived long enough
to be judged.

15:27.460 --> 15:30.750
But the truth is,
if I was in his place,

15:30.750 --> 15:32.830
I don't think I'd have done
anything different.

15:34.040 --> 15:36.330
Your grandfather
made it to 65

15:36.330 --> 15:39.380
despite everything
working against him.

15:39.380 --> 15:42.080
We need
to celebrate that.

15:42.080 --> 15:44.120
Guess I...didn't
think of it like that.

15:45.880 --> 15:47.210
Yeah, I guess
I hadn't, either.

15:50.080 --> 15:51.290
-Hey, everybody.
-Hey.

15:53.380 --> 15:55.290
Hey, Earl.
Hey, Pops.

15:57.290 --> 15:59.670
And maybe there's
some old ideas about him

15:59.670 --> 16:02.120
that I don't need
to hold on to anymore.

16:06.460 --> 16:09.120
That boy does not know
how to tell a story.

16:09.120 --> 16:10.790
Yeah, you know
a story sucks

16:10.790 --> 16:12.710
when it's about you
and you still don't care.

16:17.250 --> 16:19.580
Your birthday's
got me thinking,

16:19.580 --> 16:21.290
and I feel like I get

16:21.290 --> 16:24.330
what you've gone through
in your life better.

16:24.330 --> 16:26.790
So I just want to say
I forgive you.

16:28.120 --> 16:29.620
I don't know
what to say.

16:29.620 --> 16:32.040
Don't worry about
what to say, all right?

16:32.040 --> 16:34.670
Because my issues with you
are my issues, all right?

16:34.670 --> 16:36.040
And I'm past them.

16:36.040 --> 16:39.080
You were the man that you
had to be, and I get that now.

16:39.080 --> 16:41.420
No, I'm saying, "I don't
know what the hell
you talkin' about."

16:41.420 --> 16:42.420
What?

16:42.420 --> 16:44.830
I don't need
your forgiveness, boy!

16:44.830 --> 16:46.710
I'm the oldest living
black man.

16:46.710 --> 16:48.420
Smokey!
Put that down!

16:48.420 --> 16:50.120
Let's get back
to the track.

16:50.120 --> 16:51.790
You forgive me?
Heh!

16:51.790 --> 16:53.500
Where's my sword?!

16:53.500 --> 16:56.290
♪♪

17:00.830 --> 17:02.790
You will never believe
what my father did, Bo--

17:03.750 --> 17:05.040
Bow?

17:05.040 --> 17:06.120
Rainbow:
Are you alone?

17:08.790 --> 17:09.960
Is it just you?

17:09.960 --> 17:10.710
What are you doing?

17:10.710 --> 17:12.920
I am not...

17:12.920 --> 17:15.540
hiding from
our children.

17:15.540 --> 17:16.420
So...

17:18.170 --> 17:19.710
...what happened
with Pops?

17:19.710 --> 17:21.540
I forgave him for being
such a bad dad.

17:21.540 --> 17:22.540
Mm-hmm.

17:22.540 --> 17:24.500
And he clowned me.

17:24.500 --> 17:27.000
What'd you think
was gonna happen, Dre?

17:27.000 --> 17:29.000
Did you think he was
gonna hug you and cry

17:29.000 --> 17:30.420
and invite you
to go to all 30

17:30.420 --> 17:32.290
of the major league ballparks
with him?

17:32.290 --> 17:33.620
No.

17:33.620 --> 17:36.080
We can't do all 30.
He's not allowed back in Canada.

17:37.420 --> 17:40.080
Bow, I forgave him.
That's a big deal.

17:40.080 --> 17:42.040
Yeah, it is.

17:42.040 --> 17:44.420
And you know
what you got?

17:44.420 --> 17:48.420
You got a gift
on your dad's birthday.

17:48.420 --> 17:50.170
You forgave him, Dre.

17:50.170 --> 17:53.540
And I get that he wasn't
able to listen, but...

17:53.540 --> 17:55.500
forgiveness is about
healing what's inside you.

17:55.500 --> 17:56.330
It's not about him.

17:58.290 --> 18:00.210
Plus, you got to spend
really good time with Junior.

18:00.210 --> 18:02.040
Well...

18:02.040 --> 18:03.670
everything
has its price.

18:03.670 --> 18:05.670
I'm serious --
you need to appreciate

18:05.670 --> 18:07.460
the relationship you have
with your father.

18:07.460 --> 18:11.580
He is here for you now,
and he's a solid grandfather.

18:11.580 --> 18:13.830
So forget who he was

18:13.830 --> 18:16.710
so that you can enjoy
who he is now.

18:16.710 --> 18:18.290
Okay?

18:18.290 --> 18:19.120
Okay.

18:19.120 --> 18:20.790
Okay.

18:24.290 --> 18:27.210
I just need
30 more minutes of quiet.

18:27.210 --> 18:28.620
Just 30.
Okay, babe.

18:28.620 --> 18:29.670
Oh, God.

18:29.670 --> 18:31.330
I got you.
Just a little nap.

18:31.330 --> 18:32.170
Hey. Hey.

18:33.380 --> 18:34.420
I love you.

18:34.420 --> 18:35.540
I love you more.

18:38.080 --> 18:40.040
Your mom's hiding
in the closet!

18:43.080 --> 18:44.210
Jack: Hey, Mom.

18:46.420 --> 18:47.670
Mom?

18:47.670 --> 18:51.120
♪♪

18:51.120 --> 18:53.000
Why are you
crawling around?

18:53.000 --> 18:56.040
I was looking
for my contact.

18:56.040 --> 18:59.830
Then I was...looking
for the back of my earring...

18:59.830 --> 19:02.250
and then a Xanax --
which I'm gonna need

19:02.250 --> 19:04.790
if you guys keep asking me
"yes" or "no" questions.

19:04.790 --> 19:06.120
Uh,
what's going on?

19:07.960 --> 19:11.040
You know how I'm always trying
to be like Shonda Rhimes?

19:11.040 --> 19:13.210
Both: Uh-huh.
Okay.

19:13.210 --> 19:16.290
Well, like Shonda Rhimes,
I've been saying "Yes"

19:16.290 --> 19:17.540
to everything
that you guys ask

19:17.540 --> 19:19.710
because I just
feel guilty

19:19.710 --> 19:22.040
that I'm not
spending enough time

19:22.040 --> 19:23.620
having fun
with you guys.

19:23.620 --> 19:26.120
Mom! We have fun
with you.

19:26.120 --> 19:28.000
You have lots of fun
with me?

19:28.000 --> 19:29.920
Fun -- period.

19:29.920 --> 19:31.500
Please don't put words
in my mouth.

19:31.500 --> 19:33.000
Sorry.

19:33.000 --> 19:34.920
Yes.

19:34.920 --> 19:36.620
We have lots of fun
with you.

19:36.620 --> 19:38.210
Good, 'cause I love
playing with you guys.

19:38.210 --> 19:40.040
I just -- I just
don't have enough energy.

19:41.290 --> 19:44.040
Good, 'cause
we can use a break.

19:44.040 --> 19:45.790
Oh.
These were
just polite offers

19:45.790 --> 19:47.620
that we didn't expect you
to take us up on.

19:47.620 --> 19:50.080
Oh. Okay.

19:50.080 --> 19:52.580
I know I should've
asked this earlier,

19:52.580 --> 19:53.880
but who's Shonda Rhimes?

19:55.960 --> 19:57.420
You have
got to be kidding me.

19:57.420 --> 19:59.250
Dre: So, I took Bow's advice
to heart

19:59.250 --> 20:01.460
and decided to meet Pops
where he was --

20:01.460 --> 20:03.620
which, in this case,
happened to be the track.

20:04.880 --> 20:06.620
Oh. Hey, Pops.

20:06.620 --> 20:08.620
Hey.

20:08.620 --> 20:09.710
What you doin' here?

20:09.710 --> 20:11.330
Well,
it's your birthday,

20:11.330 --> 20:12.790
and I wanted to spend it
with you.

20:12.790 --> 20:14.120
No strings attached.

20:16.080 --> 20:17.120
Plus...

20:18.500 --> 20:19.620
...I wanted
to give you that.

20:22.040 --> 20:23.960
Money.
Uh-huh. Yeah.

20:23.960 --> 20:25.040
My favorite, son!

20:25.040 --> 20:27.120
Yeah, I knew
you'd like it.

20:27.120 --> 20:29.000
Ha ha!
Happy Birthday, Pops.

20:29.000 --> 20:31.170
Hey. I'm glad
you made it to 65.

20:32.500 --> 20:34.750
Thank you, son.
Thank you very much.

20:34.750 --> 20:35.960
Hey, hey.
What?

20:35.960 --> 20:37.080
That looks like my watch.

20:37.080 --> 20:38.580
No, this?
Uh-huh.

20:38.580 --> 20:40.710
No, no, no, no.
I got that from Smokey.

20:40.710 --> 20:42.000
Be right back.

20:42.000 --> 20:44.330
♪♪

20:48.620 --> 20:52.500
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

20:53.750 --> 20:54.920
Yay, Pops!

20:56.580 --> 20:59.540
I'm glad
we did this, Dad.

20:59.540 --> 21:00.920
Me too.

21:00.920 --> 21:04.540
You know, what do you say
you and me hop in the car,

21:04.540 --> 21:07.920
take the top down,
head up the coast,

21:07.920 --> 21:10.210
feel the cool breeze
with Cool Breeze?

21:12.960 --> 21:14.500
We're never doing that.

21:14.500 --> 21:17.250
♪♪

21:18.460 --> 21:20.830
I forgive you, Dad.

21:20.830 --> 21:22.620
-Mom!
-Shh! Daddy's working!
